A lot of changes
A lot of changes
Updated Analytics class
Contacts now store a list of all their phone numbers.
Added a fragment to allow the user to choose the phone number they wish to analyze.
Added functional loading screen for analytics class. Images have yet to be updated.
ContactPhoneNumber is now a DialogFragment. It allows the user to select which phone number they wish to analyze.
Merge conflicts resolved.
Fixed the null error that was affecting contacts with 0 messages. A dialog box now appears, informing the user that there are no messages.
Added a loading button in LoadingFragment. Button has an issue: requires 2 clicks.
Fixed loading screen, made image scalable by creating a nine patch drawable.
Added screen for total messages and total conversations. Installed font family "Oswald"
Finished Emoticon Statistics fragment.
Modified font and color of MessageLengthFragment.java
Modified some fonts, changed some colors.
Minor UI modifications
Updated loading screen. Designed by Susie Liu.
Updated conversation threshold and response threshold. Instead of setting it as a fixed value, percentiles were used.
Added DateFrequency class for line graph.
Modified the response time fragment.
Fixed the issue where app would reload every time the user clicked the back button on the contacts fragment.
Added HourFrequency fragment and method for calculating number of received and sent messages at different times of the day.
Changed loading screen, application icon. Created Settings Fragment.
Added settings screen, modified loading screen.
Modified loading screen image
Commented analytics
Prepared application for release
